  "text": "It has been proposed that medium pH is an important factor determining the cell expansion rate in tissues that can elongate rapidly in response to auxin (Schenck et al., 2010, and refs. therein) . We thus investigated whether aha2 mutant hypocotyls behave differently from wildtype hypocotyls at higher external pH, pH 7.5 or 9.5. The seedlings were grown under low blue light or in darkness. As shown in Figure 4 , D and E, the hypocotyl length of aha2-4 and aha2-5 mutants at higher pH does not differ from that of the wild-type plants, which is distinct from the strong effect elicited by changes in pH seen in roots [CITATION_1] .",
